metadata.name: Cuban nights
metadata.description:
PHOTO

The photo has been captured along the Malecon in Havana, it was 5 a.m and I was starting a documentary showing the wake up of this amazing cuban city.
I met a few fishermen going to start their day, a few people running along the Malecon and others stopping to stretch out.
When I saw this girl stopping I set the tripod and hoped to be able to capture her, without too much motion, and the seaside, the lights of the city.
This is a long exposure, despite I had to keep it as short as possible to avoid a ghostly figure.

Havana - Cuba
